# LangGraph multi-agent folder blueprint

When adding agents or services, mirror `PO Parsing AI Agent/Description/FOLDER_STRUCTURE.md` (also copied to `apps/agents/docs/shared/FOLDER_STRUCTURE.md`).

## New agent under `apps/agents/src/<agent>/`

- `<agent>.py` — exports `graph`
- `graph_builder.py`, `configuration.py`, `settings.py`
- `nodes/`, `prompts/`, `schemas/`, `tools/` (optional)

Register in `apps/agents/langgraph.json` and add routes lazily in `src/api/main.py`.

## New shared service under `apps/agents/src/services/<name>/`

- `__init__.py`, `client.py`, `settings.py`
- Add env keys to `ROOT/.env` and `.env.example`

## Rule of thumb

Shared API clients → `services/`. LLM-exposed tools used by one agent → that agent's `tools/`.
